You catuiosly Approach the old man. He lifts his head, having finaly notice you. Bevor you can speek however, you are taken aback by the mans apperance. The old and wether worn skinn looks exactly like the leather, binding the book on your leftâ€¦ But what really strikes you, are the old, dead Looking eyes. You think to yourself, you are Looking straight into nothingness. The old man starts to speek: "Welcome" he croaks, in a rather high but very week and raspy voice. "Thank you, for Talking to me, I have been alone for a verly long time"